Car Sales data is derived from https://www.odd.org.tr/web_2837_1/neuralnetwork.aspx?type=35 While rest of sets is obtained from https://evds2.tcmb.gov.tr/ Related key words search is done from Google Trends. Related box plot, correlation plot, correlation calculations are done to be able to make interpretation.

INTRODUCTION

Vehicles are known as property that people prioritize generally right after buying house or sometimes the opposite is the case. With the increase in technology and manufacturing techniques, production of vehicles is being done not only in abroad but also in Turkey. Despite of the increase in the local production, small parts of the vehicles come from abroad which makes its price dependent to exchange rate. Therefore, changes in exchange rate have an effect on the vehicle prices which contribute to the number of vehicles sold in a period. Changes in the prices of goods and services are referred as inflation, which is basically decrease in the purchasing power of money. Customer price index is one of the ways of measuring inflation over a given period. Customer price index for vehicles shows the changes in the prices of the vehicles. Increasing trend of the vehicles’ price can be shown by CPI.

With the increasing price level, people consider banks as a solution. Banks are the situations whose working principle is basically giving money to the customer right now and taking it back later with some interest rate. This enables customer, who is willing to buy something with the money they do not have at that moment, to buy that product. Banks have loan types for specific products such as housing loans, vehicle loans and so on. This is highly preferred way of buying relatively high valued products such as vehicle. Due to the fact that buying a vehicle with increased price level without any money support is not that easy, taking a loan from a bank is a popular solution. Therefore, it may be suggested that, number of vehicles sold in a period is somehow related to amount of vehicle credit taken as well as changes in exchange rate.

The research question can be stated as “Are there any correlation between sales amount of vehicles, CPI of vehicles, the total amount of credits taken and Euro Exchange Rate(TRY)?”

Selected key words are “vehicle price”(araç fiyatı), “vehicle credit”(araba kredisi) ," Vehicle sales(araç satışı)"

At the end, correlations between data sets and the amount of key word search obtained from Google Trend will be examined.

DATA VISUALIZATION

Histograms and boxplots of the data is drawn to be able to anaylze data.

ggplot(Vehicle_loan,aes(x=Month,y=values))+ geom_bar(stat='identity')+
  facet_wrap(~year(Tarih))+
  xlab("Years") + ylab("Vehicle Loan")+ ggtitle("Vehicle Loan in Turkey for 2016 to 2018")

ggplot(Euro_rate,aes(x=factor(year(Tarih)),y=values)) + geom_boxplot(aes(fill=factor(year(Tarih))))+
  xlab('Years') + 
  ylab('Euro Exchange Rate') +
  ggtitle('Euro Exchange Rate(TRY) Boxplot from 2016 to the Beginning of the 2019') +
  theme(legend.position = 'None')

Both boxplot and histogram gives the Euro Exchange Rate changes from 2016 to the end of the 2018. There has been an considerable increase when boxplot’s mean values are observed. By looking at the histograms, changes of exchange rate for each month can be seen. Besides, at the boxplots, as the time goes, height of the boxplots increases which represents the changes in the Exchange Rate in that year. 2018 is the year at which exchange rate reaches its maximum level and the maximum difference is observed.

The amount of sold vehicle in the given year is visualized by the histograms and boxplots. 2016 and 2017 behaves similar with respect to their sales while at 2018 there has been a considerable decrease in sales. However, having high sales amount at the last months of the year is common alhtough three of them have different values. 2017 is the year at which we observe similar sales amount among months, on the contrary at 2018, in addition to the low level sales, there is a hgih difference between the months. Opposite behaviours of the histograms can be seen, if vehicle sales and exchange rate histograms are compared.

As mentioned below, banks provide speacial type of loans depending on customers’ necessity. The histogram above represent the amount of vehicle loan obtained by the people. Until Sepmteber 2018, there is an increasing trend. September 2018 is also the month at which sudden increase in Euro Exchange is occured.Since exchange rate affects the interest rates, increase of euro may cause intereset rate of vehicle loan to increase at the same time which also affects the people who plan to take a loan negatively. It can be seen from the boxplot that amount of vehicle loan taken by people changes at most 2018.

Price index is the measurement of the price changes in the given product at given periods. In the histogram, increasing trend of the vehicle price level can be seen. On September 2018 there is an considerable increase in price level, which may be one the results of the Euro exchange rate increase. Since some of the vehicles are imported from abroad which makes their prices Euro indexed, the others which produced in Turkey is consists of parts which are also imported from different countries. In both cases, the price level of vehicles is affected by the exchange rate. Similar behaviour of the price index and vehicle credit can be also observed by looking at their histograms. Till 09.2018 both of them keeps increasing, after that months, they both start decreasing. Reason might be the following, increasing price level of vehicles obliges people to get money support and vehicle loan is one of the limited money support options.

GOOGLE TRENDS

Taşıt Fiyatı is a key word that is used by the potential customers and the certain customers. It can be observed that data is fluctuating, so there is not a trend. As can be seen from the histogram and boxplot, at 2018, there is not high fluctuating in the data and median has higher value compare to other two. Its reason may be the increase in vehicles prices. Ad prices increases people tend to know more about the current prices.

As previous keyword, in this keyword also, searching amount of this keyword is also fluctuating.For the 2018, there is decrease in the mean value, which may be result of increasing prices of vehicle.

Taşıt kredisi search does not fluctuate as much as previous two keywords. As Euro exchange rate increases, price index increases which leads people to search more about vehicle loans. Since loan is a solution for high price level, people follow loan opportunities more to be able to afford high price level.

CONCLUSION

The histograms and boxplot we got with the selected data sets helps us to visualize relationship between data sets. In this study, after looking at the behavior of the data sets, we realized that there is a strong correlation between Euro exchange rate, vehicle price index and vehicle loan. As expected, there is negative correlation between vehicle sale and price index. Surprisingly, the number of search for “vehicle sale” and actual vehicle sales is almost 0 correlated. One possible reason may be the fact that people do not incline to buy vehicles from web sites, therefore, who are buying vehicles may not prefer Google. Keyword sales price is also not correlated, almost 0. The amount of searches done by people for the keyword “vehicle loan” has not very high but positive correlation with Euro exchange rate, vehicle loan amount and vehicle sales amount.

It is also important to remember that while interpreting the relationship between data sets, there lots fo thing that we ignore.
